QUEUE:
It follows FIFO logic

Enqueue: Add an element at the rear.

Dequeue: Remove an element from the front.

Peek/Front: Look at the front element without removing it.

isEmpty: Check if the queue is empty.

isFull (for fixed-size queues): Check if the queue is full.


📌 Real-World Use Cases
Task Scheduling: OS process scheduling uses queues (ready queue, waiting queue).

Printers: Print jobs are queued in order of arrival.

Networking: Packets are queued before transmission.

Customer Service Systems: Calls or requests are handled in the order they arrive.

Breadth-First Search (BFS): Graph traversal uses queues to explore nodes level by level.